          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript employed for private consultation and dedicated to the rites of bathing during the month of Māgha (January/February). May be part of a larger text called the Māghamāhātmya (Greatness of the month of Māgha). Rites and prayers are to be performed for the removal of sin and for attaining liberation, before sunrise, in a sacred river and are directed at various gods, especially Viṣṇu, such as in his demon-destroying form of Madhusūdana (f. 2v). Manuscript lacks an end.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
